HEADWORD: aquaculture
<hw>aquaculture</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the cultivation of
aquatic animals, such as fish or shellfish, or of plants, such as
seaweed, in a controlled and sometimes enclosed body of water. The term
includes use of either salt or fresh water. It is a form of agriculture,
but under water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aqua fortis</ent>⟦br⟧
